Displaced residents say last week they attempted to occupy an unused piece of land near the city of Cape Town’s Bosasa temporary structures , but they were barred by law enforcement officers, who took down their structures. And some community leaders have vowed to support them to continue staying here until authorities provide suitable alternatives. eNCA’s Nobesuthu Hejana reports. #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - The City of Cape Town is planning to evict displaced flood victims from the Mfuleni Community Hall. About 60 families occupied the building after their homes in the Burundi settlement were destroyed by floods. They say they will not leave until alternate arrangements are made. The city says talks with the community have been unsuccessful. * eNCA’s Nobesuthu Hejana reports.